data.description: HIGHLY sought-after location on the west side of downtown Loveland! Situated in the 2 blocks of beautiful Craftsman style brick bungalows that make up The West 4th St Historic District. Built by William W. Green in the early 1920's, this neighborhood is one of Loveland's most beloved gems. Friendly front porch greets you as you enter through the glass front doors. Large living & dining areas with hardwood floors throughout. Cute 11x11 sunroom overlooking 4th St. Kitchen has been recently updated w/ pretty Quartz countertops and Subway tile. Plenty of cabinet & counter space. All appliances included. Some newer light fixtures on the main level. The basement has a large bedroom, huge 3/4 bath, laundry, & lots of storage. Enjoy the wonderful outdoor living space from the patio & Trex deck in the fully fenced yard. Nice mountain views from the backyard. Alley access. New roof in 2022. Enjoy breathtaking sunsets from the curve at the end of the street overlooking pastures, The Big Thompson River, Centennial Ball Fields, & spectacular mountain views. Just blocks from all that  downtown Loveland has to offer & River's Edge Natural Area. No HOA or Metro District. Take advantage of this rare opportunity in downtown Loveland TODAY!
